          <!-- .article-category -->
                    <div class="article-date">
            21 February 2014          </div>
                              <h1  class="title inf_class" data-analyticsid="/lifestyle/2014/02/why-we-must-destroy-myth-miscarriage-failure"><!-- @Title --> Why we must destroy the myth of miscarriage as women&#039;s “failure”</h1>
          <span property="dc:title" content="Why we must destroy the myth of miscarriage as women&#039;s “failure”" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span><div class="field field-name-field-subheadline field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>Knowing how common miscarriage is – an estimated one in four pregnancies end this way – doesn’t stop you from feeling guilty.</p>
</div></div></div> 
		
        
            
		  
		  </header>
        <aside class="large-3 columns article-author" style="padding-bottom:0;">
                    <div class="multiple-author-images">
                        <div class="author-avatar" ><img src="https://www.newstatesman.com/sites/default/files/victoriads.jpg"></div>
